messages.title: A Strong Local Voice for Colchester
messages.content: Your four commitments from Will Quince - A strong local voice, standing up for our town.

keyPolicies.policyDescription: Pushing for fairer funding for every school.
Fighting for our share of the extra £8bn for the NHS and backing our GPs.
Working hard for new trains, more reliable services and fairer fares.
Improvements to the A120, A12 and junction 28 of the M25.

issues.education: Pushing for fairer funding for every school.
issues.health: Fighting for our share of the extra £8bn for the NHS and backing our GPs. Colchester Hospital priority. Getting out of special measures.

leaflet.personalStatement: I’ve lived in Colchester for over 10 years and it’s where my wife and I are raising our young family. I know first-hand the issues facing families and residents.

images.caption: Will Quince with another individual discussing issues.

leaflet.additionalNotes: Leaflet mostly focuses on Colchester specific issues and improvements.
